lona]]\n| Ir\u00e1n Pont Gil \n| '''Top 10''' \n| \n|-\n|-style=\"background-color:#FFFF99;\"\n| 1985 \n| [[Arag\u00f3n]]\n| Beatriz Molero Beltr\u00e1n \n| '''Top 10''' \n| \n|-\n|-style=\"background-color:#FFFF99;\"\n| 1984 \n| [[Seville]] \n| Soledad Marisol Pila Balanza \n| '''Top 10''' \n| \n|-\n|-style=\"background-color:#FFFF99;\"\n| 1983 \n| [[Las Palmas]]\n| Milagros P\u00e9rez Castro \n| '''Top 10''' \n| \n|-\n|-style=\"background-color:#FFFF66;\"\n| 1982 \n| [[Alicante]]\n| Mar\u00eda del Carmen Arqu\u00e9s \n| '''1st Runner-up''' \n| \n|-\n| 1981 \n| [[Las Palmas]] \n| [[Frances Ondiviela|Francisca Ondiviela]]  \n| Unplaced \n| \n|-\n|-style=\"background-color:#FFFF66;\"\n| 1980 \n| [[Barcelona]]\n| Mar\u00eda Agustina Garc\u00eda \n| '''2nd Runner-up''' \n| \n|-\n| 1979 \n| [[Asturias]] \n| Yolanda Maria Hoyos  \n| Unplaced \n|  \n|-\n| 1978 \n| [[Andalusia]] \n| Maria Inmaculada Arencibia \n| Unplaced \n| \n|-\n|-style=\"background-color:GOLD; font-weight: bold\"\n| 1977 \n| [[Madrid]]\n| [[Pilar Medina]] \n| [[Miss International 1977]] \n| Best National Costume \n|-\n| 1976 \n| [[Tenerife]] \n| Victoria Mart\u00edn Gonz\u00e1lez\n| Unplaced \n| \n|-\n| 1975 \n| [[Catalu\u00f1a]]\n| Maria Teresa Maldonado \n| Unplaced \n| \n|-\n|-style=\"background-color:#FFFF99;\"\n| 1974 \n| [[Balearic Islands]]\n| Consuelo Mart\u00edn L\u00f3pez \n| '''Top 15''' \n| \n|-\n|-style=\"background-color:#FFFF66;\"\n| 1973 \n| [[Las Palmas]]\n| Maria Isabel Lorenzo \n| '''2nd Runner-up''' \n| '''Miss Photogenic'''\n|-\n| 1972 \n| [[Malaga]]\n| Gloria Puyol Toledo  \n| Unplaced \n| \n|-\n| 1971 \n| \u2014\n| Consuelo Varela Costales    \n| Unplaced \n| \n|-\n| 1970 \n| [[Madrid]] \n| Mar\u00eda Margarita Garc\u00eda  \n| Unplaced \n|  \n|-\n|-style=\"background-color:#FFFF99;\"\n| 1969  \n| [[Las Palmas]]\n| Mery de Lara Caballero \n| '''Top 15''' \n| \n|-\n| 1968 \n| [[Pais Vasco]]\n| Yolanda Legarreta Urquijo  \n| Unplaced \n| \n|-\n| 1967 \n| [[Valencia]] \n| Amparo Ruiz \n| Unplaced \n| \n|-\n| 1966\n| colspan=4 {{n/a|No contest}}\n|-\n|-style=\"background-color:#FFFF99;\"\n| 1965 \n| [[Las Palmas]]\n| Rafaela Roque S\u00e1nchez \n| '''Top 15''' \n| \n|-\n| 1964 \n| [[Tenerife]]\n| Lucia Pilar Herrera\n| Unplaced \n|  \n|-\n| 1963 \n| [[Andalusia]]  \n| Encarnaci\u00f3n Zalabardo  \n| Unplaced \n| \n|-\n|-style=\"background-color:#FFFF66;\"\n| 1961 \n| [[Catalu\u00f1a]]\n| Maria Del Carmen Fern\u00e1ndez\n| '''2nd Runner-up''' \n| \n|-\n| 1960 \n| [[Pais Vasco]]\n| Elena Herrera D\u00e1vila-N\u00fa\u00f1ez \n| Unplaced \n| \n|-\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[M\u00edster Espa\u00f1a]]\n*[[Miss Earth Spain]]\n*[[Spain at major beauty pageants]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|refs=<ref name=\"hola\">{{cite news|title=Paula Guill\u00f3, Miss Teruel, is crowned Miss Spain 2010 |url=https://translate.google.com/translate?js=n&prev=_t&hl=en&ie=UTF-8&layout=2&eotf=1&sl=es&tl=en&u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.hola.com%2Ffamosos%2F2010092645637%2Fganadora%2FMissEspana%2F2010%2F1%2F|accessdate=2010-10-10|newspaper=[[\u00a1Hola!]]|date=September 26, 2010}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"canarias7\">{{cite news|title=Miss Tenerife is crowned Miss Spain|url=https://translate.google.com/translate?js=n&prev=_t&hl=en&ie=UTF-8&layout=2&eotf=1&sl=es&tl=en&u=http://www.canarias7.es/articulo.cfm%3Fid%3D86325&act=url|accessdate=21 October 2010|newspaper=[[Canarias7]]|date=March 2, 2010|agency=[[EFE]]}}</ref>\n\n}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Portal|Spain}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20160507103912/http://bemiss.es/ bemiss.es (Miss Universe Spain)]\n* [http://www.lempimissit.suntuubi.com/ MISS ESPANA]\n* [https://www.nuestrabellezaespana.com/ Miss World Spain and Miss International Spain]\n{{Miss Spain}}\n{{Miss Spain winners in the Grand Slam pageants}}\n{{Beauty contests in Europe}}\n{{Miss Universe countries and territories}}\n{{Miss World countries and territories}}\n{{Miss International countries and territories}}\n\n[[Category:Miss Spain]]\n[[Category:Miss Universe by country|Spain]]\n[[Category:Beauty pageants in Spain|Spain]]\n[[Category:Recurring events established in 1929]]\n[[Category:Spanish awards]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|National beauty pageant competition in Spain, founded in 1929}}\n{{Infobox organization\n| name = Miss Spain<br />Miss Espa\u00f1a\n| motto = Beauty, Elegance, Personality, Class, Poise, Communication and Safety\n| formation = 1929\n| type = [[Beauty pageant]]\n| headquarters = [[Madrid]]\n| location = [[Spain]]\n| membership = {{Hlist|[[Miss Universe]]|[[Miss World]]|[[Miss International]]}}\n| language = [[Spanish language|Spanish]]\n| leader_title = National Director\n| leader_name = Jorge Diez Vanila (Miss Universe Spain)<br>Cres del Olmo & Daniel Montesdeoca (Miss World Spain)\n| key_people = \n| num_staff = \n| budget = \n| website = [https://www.missuniversespain.org/ Miss Universe Spain]<br>[https://www.nuestrabellezaespana.com/ Miss World Spain]\n}}\n\n'''Miss Spain''' ([[Spanish language|Spanish]]: Miss Espa\u00f1a) is a national [[beauty pageant]] in [[Spain]] that selects Spanish representatives to compete in three of the [[Big Four international beauty pageants|big four]] major international beauty pageants: the [[Miss Universe]], [[Miss World]], and [[Miss International]] competitions.\n\n==History==\n{| class=\"toccolours\" style=\"width: 20em; float:right; margin-left:1em; font-size:83%; line-height:1.3em; width:30%;\"\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" | <hr />\n|-\n! colspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:center; background:#FFDDCA;\" | Number of Wins under Miss Espa\u00f1a Organization (Miss Universe Spain)\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" | <hr />\n|-\n! colspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | Current franchises\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Pageant !! Title !! {{nowrap|Winning year(s)}}\n|-\n| [[Miss Universe]] || 1 || 1974\n|-\n| [[Miss World]] || 1 || 2015\n|-\n| [[Miss International]] || 3 || 1977, 1990, 2008\n|-\n| [[Miss Europe]] || 5 || 1962, 1967, 1970, 1974, 1985\n|-\n|}\n\n===Miss Spain: 1929-2011===\nThe origins of Miss Spain date back to 1929, when early contests took place until the advent of civil war in 1936, followed by the dictatorship of [[Francisco Franco]], which did not permit beauty pageants until 1961.\n\nThe winner of Miss Spain is sent to represent her country in Miss Universe. However, if Miss Spain is underage, a runner-up is sent to Miss Universe. Overall in these international pageants, Spain's success has been moderate with one Miss Universe title in [[Miss Universe 1974|1974]] and 3 Miss International titles in [[Miss International 1977|1977]], [[Miss International 1990|1990]] and [[Miss International 2008|2008]].\n\n===Miss Universe Spain and Miss World Spain: 2013-present===\nAfter the inactivity of Miss Spain contest, the company Be Beautiful Spain, S.L. was created by Guillermo Escobar Garc\u00eda, former worker of Miss Spain and who founded the contests Miss Spain Universe and Miss Spain World. In 2013, the pageant is separated into several pageants - like Miss World Spain and Miss Universe Spain. In the year 2018, after seven years of inactivity, the contest '''Miss Spain''' returns with Pedro Quesada as president and with [[Juncal Rivero]] as general director. The current national director for Spain at Miss Universe is Jorge Diez Vanila. The national directors for Spain at both Miss World and Miss International are Cres del Olmo and Daniel Montesdeoca.\n\n==Titleholders==\n::''The winner of Miss Espa\u00f1a represents her country at [[Miss Universe]]. On occasion, when the winner does not qualify (due to age) for either contest, a runner-up is sent. Sometimes, the winner can also compete at [[Miss World]] and [[Miss Europe]] if the winner will be available to compete by the Miss Espa\u00f1a Organization. However, Miss Espa\u00f1a Organization was claimed to bankrupt in 2012, and separated into several independent contests choosing the representatives in the International beauty pageants like Miss World Spain (Miss Espa\u00f1a Mundo) and Miss Universe Spain (Miss Espa\u00f1a Universo).''\n\n===1929-2011===\n{| class=\"sortable\" border=\"5\" cellpadding=\"3\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #FFFFFF; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%; text-align:center\"\n|- \n!width=\"60\"|Year||width=\"300\"|Miss Espa\u00f1a / Miss Spain||width=\"200\"|Autonomous Community||width=\"300\"|Notes\n|-\n| 1929\n| Pepita Samper \u2020\n| [[Valencia (province)|Valencia]]\n| \n|-\n| 1930\n| Elena Pla \u2020\n| [[Valencia (province)|Valencia]]\n| \n|-\n| 1931\n| Ermelina Carre\u00f1o \u2020\n| [[Ciudad Real (province)|Ciudad Real]]\n| \n|-\n| 1932\n| Teresita Daniel \n| [[Barcelona (province)|Barcelona]]\n| \n|-\n| 1933\n| Emilia Docet \n| [[Pontevedra (province)|Pontevedra]]\n| \n|-\n|-style=\"background-color:GOLD; font-weight: bold\"\n| 1935\n| Alicia Navarro <ref>{{cite book | last=Payne | first=S.G. | title=Spain's First Democracy: The Second Republic, 1931-1936 | publisher=University of Wisconsin Press | year=1993 | isbn=978-0-299-13674-1 | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=46N-pNbNG2kC&pg=PA256 | page=256}}</ref>\n| [[Tenerife (province)|Tenerife]]\n| [[Miss Europe|Miss Europe 1935]]\n|-\n| 1934\n| |Mar\u00eda Eugenia Henr\u00edquez Gir\u00f3n\n| [[Community of Madrid|Madrid]]\n| \n|-\n| 1959\n| Salud Rubio Perez-Grueso\n| [[Toledo (province)|Toledo]]\n| \n|-\n| 1960\n| Teresa Del Rio\n| [[M\u00e1laga (province)|M\u00e1laga]]\n| \n|-\n| 1961\n| Mar\u00eda del [[Carmen Cervera]] <ref>{{cite book | last=Gayesky | first=F. | last2=Gorman | first2=E. | last3=Luna | first3=K. | last4=Legaspi | first4=A. | title=MTV Spain | publisher=Wiley | series=MTV Guides | year=2007 | isbn=978-0-7645-8772-6 | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Owa_0MppHm4C&pg=PA124 | page=124}}</ref>\n| [[Barcelona (province)|Barcelona]]\n| \n|-\n|-style=\"background-color:GOLD; font-weight: bold\"\n| 1962\n| Maruja Garc\u00eda Nicolau\n| [[Balearic Islands|Islas Baleares]]\n| [[Mi