rieto]] \u2014 Miss Universo Espa\u00f1a\n| [[Province of Albacete|Albacete]]\n|\n|-\n| Maria Elisabeth Tuli\u00e1n Mar\u00edn \u2014 Miss Mundo Espa\u00f1a\n| [[Balearic Islands|Islas Baleares]]\n| {{n/a|Nuestra Belleza Espa\u00f1a Organization \u2014 Cres del Olmo and Daniel Montesdeoca Directorship \u00b7 New License holders for Spain at Miss World}}\n|- \n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[Miss Universe Spain 2018|2018]]<sup>[[Miss World Spain 2018|W]]</sup>\n| [[\u00c1ngela Ponce|\u00c1ngela Ponce Camacho]] \u2014 Miss Universo Espa\u00f1a\n| [[Seville]]\n| {{n/a|First transgender woman to compete in Miss Universe}}\n|-\n| Amaia Izar \u2014 Miss Mundo Espa\u00f1a\n| [[Navarre]]\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[Miss Universe Spain 2019|2019]]<sup>[[Miss World Spain 2019|W]]</sup>\n| Natalie Ortega Tafjord \u2014 Miss Universo Espa\u00f1a\n| [[Barcelona]]\n| {{n/a|Be Miss Organization \u2014 Jorge Diez Vanila Directorship \u00b7 The 1st Miss Universo Espa\u00f1a who is of Spanish and Norwegian descents}}\n|-\n| Mar\u00eda Del Mar Aguilera Zuheros \u2014 Miss Mundo Espa\u00f1a\n| [[Province of C\u00f3rdoba (Spain)|C\u00f3rdoba]]\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|2020\n| TBA \u2014 Miss Universo Espa\u00f1a\n| TBA\n| \n|-\n| TBA \u2014 Miss Mundo Espa\u00f1a\n| TBA\n|\n|- \n|}\n{{note label|note01|A|}}''Resigned''<br />\n{{note label|note02|B|}}''Took over title''<br />\n{{note label|note03|C|}}''Patricia Yurena Rodr\u00edguez originally won Miss Spain 2008 but due to age requirements was unable to compete at Miss Universe and was subsequently replaced by Claudia Moro. Rodr\u00edguez instead represented Spain at Miss World. Rodr\u00edguez later won Miss Universe Spain 2013 represented Spain at Miss Universe 2013.''\n\n==Ranking==\n===Miss Spain===\n{| class=\"sortable\" border=\"5\" cellpadding=\"3\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #FFFFFF; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%; text-align:center\"\n|- \n!width=\"50\"|Title||width=\"250\"|Aut