000 \nFile:Lorena Bernal 2007.jpg| [[Lorena Bernal|Lorena Bernal Pascual]], Miss Spain 1999\nFile:Garbi\u00f1e Abasolo.jpg| [[Garbi\u00f1e Abasolo]], Miss Spain 1983\nFile:Carmen Cervera. Inauguracion Thyssen M\u00e1laga.jpg| [[Carmen Cervera]], Miss Spain 1961\nFile:Pepita Samper.JPG|[[Pepita Samper]], Miss Spain 1929\n</gallery>\n\n==Big Four pageants representatives==\n===Miss Universo Espa\u00f1a===\n{{plainlist|\n* {{Color box|gold|border=black}} : Declared as Winner\n* {{Color box|#FFFF66|border=black}} : Ended as runner-up or top 5/6 qualification\n* {{Color box|#FFFF99|border=black}} : Ended as one of the finalists or semifinalists\n* {{Color box|#FADADD|border=black}} : Ended as special awards winner\n}}\n::''The '''winner''' of Miss Spain represents her country at the [[Miss Universe]]. On occasion, when the winner does not qualify (due to age) for either contest, a runner-up is sent. Since 2013 the BE MISS ORG. took over the franchise of Miss Universe and the winner of Be Miss Universo Espa\u00f1a participates at Miss Universe competition.''\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" border=\"5\" cellpadding=\"3\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #FFFFFF; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 92%; text-align:center\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#787878\" colspan=10 align=\"center\"\n|width=\"60\"|<span style=\"color:white\">Year</span>\n|width=\"230\"|<span style=\"color:white\">Autonomous Community</span>\n|width=\"250\"|<span style=\"color:white\">Be Miss Universo Espa\u00f1a</span>\n|width=\"250\"|<span style=\"color:white\">Placement at Miss Universe</span>\n|width=\"230\"|<span style=\"color:white\">Special Awards</span> \n|-\n| 2020 \n| TBA\n| TBA\n| TBA\n| TBA \n|-\n| 2019 \n| [[Barcelona]]\n| Natalie Ortega Tafjord\n| Unplaced\n| \n|-\n| 2018\n| [[Province of Seville|Seville]]\n| [[\u00c1ngela Ponce|\u00c1ngela Ponce Camacho]]\n| Unplaced\n| \n|-\n|-style=\"background-color:#FFFF99;\"\n| 2017\n| [[Albacete (province)|Albacete]