s Espa\u00f1a was bankruptcy.''\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" border=\"5\" cellpadding=\"3\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #FFFFFF; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 92%; text-align:center\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#787878\" colspan=10 align=\"center\"\n|width=\"60\"|<span style=\"color:white\">Year</span>\n|width=\"230\"|<span style=\"color:white\">Autonomous Community</span>\n|width=\"250\"|<span style=\"color:white\">Miss Mundo Espa\u00f1a</span>\n|width=\"250\"|<span style=\"color:white\">Placement at Miss World</span>\n|width=\"230\"|<span style=\"color:white\">Special Awards</span> \n|-\n| 2020 \n| TBA\n| TBA\n| TBA \n| \n|-style=\"background-color:#FFFF99;\"\n| 2019 \n| [[C\u00f3rdoba, Spain|C\u00f3rdoba]] \n| Mar\u00eda Del Mar Aguilera\n| '''Top 40'''\n| [[Miss World Sport]] (Top 32)\n|-\n| 2018 \n| [[Navarre]]\n| Amaia Izar \n| Unplaced \n| [[Miss World Talent]] (Top 18), [[Miss World Top Model]] (Top 24)\n|-\n| 2017 \n| [[Balearic Islands]]\n| Elisa Tulian \n| Unplaced \n| [[Miss World Talent]] Top 20 \n|-\n| 2016 \n| [[Zaragoza]]\n| Raquel Tejedor \n| Unplaced \n| [[Miss World Sport]] (Top 24)\n|-\n|-style=\"background-color:GOLD; font-weight: bold\"\n| 2015 \n| [[Barcelona]]\n| [[Mireia Lalaguna]] \n| [[Miss World 2015]] \n| [[Miss World Top Model]], [[Miss World Sport]] (Top 24), [[Miss World Talent]] (Top 30)\n|-\n| 2014 \n| [[Castilla-La Mancha]]\n| Lourdes Fern\u00e1ndez\n| Unplaced\n| \n|-\n|-style=\"background-color:#FFFF66;\"\n| 2013 \n| [[Basque Country (autonomous community)|Basque]]\n| [[Elena Ibarbia|Elena Ibarbia Jim\u00e9nez]] \n| '''Top 5''' \n| [[Miss World Sports]] (1st Runner-up), [[Miss World Beach Beauty]] (Top 11)\n|-\n|-bgcolor=\"#787878\" colspan=10 align=\"center\"\n| colspan=\"5\" |<span style=\"color:white\">Spanish Representatives from Miss Espa\u00f1a</span>\n|- \n|-style=\"background-color:#FFFF99;\"\n| 2012 \n| [[Las Palmas]]\n| Ar\u00e1nzazu Est\u00e9vez Godoy \n| '''Top 15''' \n